<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="137" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="22.[140,1108,835,1179]" pageId="22" pageNumber="137">
<bibRefCitation author="Smetana" box="[185,420,941,968]" firstAuthor="Smetana" pageId="22" pageNumber="137" pagination="1 - 946" refId="ref18100" refString="Smetana A (1995) Rove beetles of the subtribe Philonthina of America north of Mexico (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae) classification, phylogeny and taxonomic revision. Memoirs on Entomology International 3: i-x, 1 - 946." type="journal article" year="1995">Smetana (1995: 96)</bibRefCitation>
wrote, “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nordman" authorityYear="1837" box="[525,723,941,967]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Philonthus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="furvus">
<emphasis box="[525,723,941,967]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="137">Philonthus furvus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a distinctly hygrophilous species, occurring in all kinds of wet habitats, such as edges of lakes and ponds, marshes and swamps, banks of rivers and creeks, wet forests, seepages, etc.” 
<bibRefCitation author="Davies" box="[941,1108,1011,1037]" firstAuthor="Davies" pageId="22" pageNumber="137" refId="ref16041" refString="Davies, A (1979. A study of the staphylinid beetles occurring in decaying seaweed on the shore of Passamaquoddy Bay (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae). BSc thesis, Ottawa, Ontario: Carleton University." type="book" year="1979">Davies (1979)</bibRefCitation>
found this species was apparently well-adapted to, and dependant on, beach-wrack environments in St. Andrews, 
<collectingRegion box="[492,681,1082,1108]" country="Canada" name="New Brunswick" pageId="22" pageNumber="137">New Brunswick</collectingRegion>
. The above records from Brier Island (NS) are from a similar environment. Its distribution in North America is shown in 
<bibRefCitation author="Smetana" box="[140,329,1152,1179]" firstAuthor="Smetana" pageId="22" pageNumber="137" pagination="1 - 946" refId="ref18100" refString="Smetana A (1995) Rove beetles of the subtribe Philonthina of America north of Mexico (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae) classification, phylogeny and taxonomic revision. Memoirs on Entomology International 3: i-x, 1 - 946." type="journal article" year="1995">Smetana (1995)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
